1
00:00:06,790 --> 00:00:09,050
The person I like...

2
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:16,220
is the person standing
right in front of me.

3
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:32,899
Huh?

4
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,449
What's with that look on your face?

5
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:37,439
Isn't that a line from the
movie we just watched?

6
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:40,370
I'm not joking.
I'm asking you seriously.

7
00:00:40,410 --> 00:00:41,410
I'm not.

8
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,060
I'm being completely serious, too.

9
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:45,710
The person right in front of me.

10
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:47,250
Huh?

11
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:51,480
But I'm the only one here.

12
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:53,340
No, I mean...

13
00:00:57,660 --> 00:01:00,220
Isn't this exactly like
the movie we just saw?

14
00:01:01,470 --> 00:01:03,020
I really do like you.

15
00:01:04,690 --> 00:01:05,690
What?

16
00:01:06,180 --> 00:01:07,180
What I mean is...

17
00:01:09,180 --> 00:01:13,540
The person I like is you,
Wataru, standing right here.

18
00:01:18,070 --> 00:01:19,070
Me?

19
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:22,449
I know the timing seems convenient,

20
00:01:22,450 --> 00:01:24,370
but I've been planning to tell you anyway.

21
00:01:27,830 --> 00:01:29,590
Then, what about before...

22
00:01:30,130 --> 00:01:32,776
They got rejected because the other
person said he liked someone else.

23
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:36,760
Apparently, everyone who confessed
got rejected for that exact reason.

24
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,990
I know this must be a shock,

25
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:44,530
but there's someone...

26
00:01:45,156 --> 00:01:47,456
I've had a crush on for a long time.

27
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,560
And that person is...

28
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,540
Wataru?

29
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:57,479
Hey, Wataru.

30
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,860
Oh, sorry.

31
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:05,300
I don't really know what to say...

32
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:08,770
Uh, do you like guys?

33
00:02:09,473 --> 00:02:11,113
Oh, that's not what I meant...

34
00:02:12,170 --> 00:02:13,370
How should I put this?

35
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:16,300
I can date girls normally,

36
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:19,010
but the one I fell for is you, Wataru.

37
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:20,970
Why me?

38
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,970
I wonder why.

39
00:02:24,286 --> 00:02:26,286
Maybe it was just meant to be.

40
00:02:29,860 --> 00:02:32,750
I see. So that's how it is.

41
00:02:36,340 --> 00:02:37,690
Thank you.

42
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:39,570
Huh? For what?

43
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:43,340
Thank you for not being disgusted or
laughing, and for listening to me seriously.

44
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:44,910
The fact that I like you...

45
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,870
Hearing you say it to my face like that...

46
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:56,900
Anyway,

47
00:02:57,460 --> 00:02:58,640
let's head back.

48
00:02:58,670 --> 00:02:59,679
Huh?

49
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,030
Let's go home.

50
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,616
It might sound weird coming from me,
but are you sure you're okay with this?

51
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,100
It's fine.

52
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,660
You don't have to worry about it, Wataru.

53
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,410
I'm not asking you to like me back.

54
00:03:15,980 --> 00:03:19,290
Just knowing how I feel
is enough for me.

55
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,840
What is that supposed to mean?

56
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:30,210
But in return, there's one favor
I'd like to ask. Would that be okay?

57
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:43,820
Sure.

58
00:03:52,060 --> 00:03:55,110
Even though his confession was so casual,

59
00:03:55,140 --> 00:03:58,140
his expression at that moment
was more sincere than ever.

60
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:02,990
I agreed before I even had time to think.

61
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:40,000
"My Summer Of You"
(Episode 2)

62
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,560
Morning.

63
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,080
Morning.

64
00:06:03,340 --> 00:06:04,420
What's with you?

65
00:06:06,070 --> 00:06:07,070
I'm just so happy.

66
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,660
Come on, cut it out.

67
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:12,630
You're going to make me feel weird too.

68
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,750
Sorry, just ignore me.

69
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:15,830
No way.

70
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:20,560
By the way, about what I asked yesterday,
are you really okay with it?

71
00:06:21,660 --> 00:06:22,660
Of course.

72
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:24,340
I keep my word.

73
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:26,420
That's so like you.

74
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:31,970
Man, I wish summer break
would hurry up and get here.

75
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:42,580
But we have exams before summer break.

76
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,879
Sekiguchi senpai, please help me out.

77
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,240
- Please!
- Let me think about it...

78
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,679
It'll cost you two
convenience store popsicles.

79
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,700
Thanks!

80
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:53,900
- Just as I thought.
- Thanks!

81
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:59,119
But Wataru, instead of asking me,

82
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:01,179
why don't you ask Saeki to tutor you?

83
00:07:01,180 --> 00:07:02,759
Wouldn't that be better?

84
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,840
But he seems pretty busy lately.

85
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,060
And aren't you being a bit prickly?

86
00:07:07,090 --> 00:07:10,090
He's definitely still sore about Saeki
beating him on the midterms.

87
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:13,510
Oh, Saeki is busy, huh?

88
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:17,999
But that guy barely even
studies for exams, right?

89
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,059
He said, "Just listening
in class is enough."

90
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:21,290
Wataru, stop rubbing it in.

91
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,400
Sigh.

92
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:31,050
Is there really absolutely nothing
I can beat him at?

93
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:35,499
That guy definitely
has a girlfriend, right?

94
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:36,700
For sure.

95
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:38,850
And she's definitely super cute.

96
00:07:39,410 --> 00:07:40,510
A total babe.

97
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:44,290
If it weren't for me... with
his looks and everything,

98
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:46,850
he could easily date anyone he wanted.

99
00:07:48,020 --> 00:07:49,629
Man, I'm so jealous.

100
00:07:49,630 --> 00:07:50,670
Just give up.

101
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,079
That's the social hierarchy for you.

102
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,679
Is that really how the hierarchy works?

103
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,919
Yep.

104
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,929
Give it up.

105
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:58,269
I'm off to change the future of Japan.

106
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,360
How did we get onto that?

107
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:04,020
But falling in love
isn't really about that, is it?

108
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,270
Man, this is tough.

109
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:09,070
Hey, we haven't even started studying yet.

110
00:08:10,820 --> 00:08:13,570
Guchi, you'll never
understand this in your lifetime.

111
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:14,840
Oh yeah?

112
00:08:15,380 --> 00:08:17,499
Then let me teach you a lesson.

113
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,500
You want a piece of this?

114
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:20,159
Oh, they're finally going at it.

115
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,539
Go, go, go!

116
00:08:21,540 --> 00:08:22,540
Alright, open your book.

117
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:24,060
No.

118
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,329
- Open it.
- No way.

119
00:08:25,330 --> 00:08:26,459
We need to study.

120
00:08:26,460 --> 00:08:27,460
I'm not studying.

121
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:52,019
A pilgrimage means visiting
the filming locations, right?

122
00:08:52,020 --> 00:08:53,020
Yeah.

123
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,920
Summer break is coming up,
so I wanted to go then.

124
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,530
Is this what you wanted to ask me?

125
00:08:58,780 --> 00:08:59,780
Yeah.

126
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:05,020
I really want to go with you.

127
00:09:06,780 --> 00:09:07,960
What do you think?

128
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:13,460
Sounds great.

129
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,610
It'll make for a wonderful summer memory.

130
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:31,180
I'll leave it at that for now, Wataru.

131
00:09:32,460 --> 00:09:33,536
- I'll text you later.
- Okay.

132
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,400
- Bye.
- See ya. Good luck with club practice.

133
00:09:39,420 --> 00:09:43,439
Ah, I'm so excited for summer break.

134
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,619
Totally. I couldn't agree more.

135
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:46,146
Toda, are you going
anywhere for summer break?

136
00:09:46,170 --> 00:09:48,199
Well, mostly working my part-time job.

137
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,840
Oh, how responsible.

138
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:50,999
Where are you working?

139
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,010
At my uncle's diner.

140
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,090
Oh...

141
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:57,180
You don't care at all, do you?

142
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:59,020
- Not really.
- Don't just say it out loud!

143
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,220
Wataru.

144
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,459
Oh, are you heading home?

145
00:10:03,460 --> 00:10:04,460
Yeah.

146
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,719
Our plans for the day after
tomorrow are still good, right?

147
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,169
Yeah. What about you, Saeki?

148
00:10:08,170 --> 00:10:09,170
I'm good to go.

149
00:10:09,660 --> 00:10:11,479
Let's meet in front of
the ticket gate at 8:00 AM.

150
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,480
Okay.

151
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,500
- Don't oversleep.
- I won't.

152
00:10:15,020 --> 00:10:17,419
- Actually, I might be too nervous to sleep.
- Huh?

153
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:18,659
See you then.

154
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:19,660
Yeah.

155
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,299
What's this? What's this?

156
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,379
What?

157
00:10:23,380 --> 00:10:26,960
What on earth could possibly keep
the great Saeki-kun awake at night?

158
00:10:27,180 --> 00:10:28,520
What's that supposed to mean?

159
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:31,079
We're just going on a film pilgrimage.

160
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:34,359
A pilgrimage?
Like for an anime or a movie?

161
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:37,019
Yeah, we both like the same movie.

162
00:10:37,020 --> 00:10:39,970
I see. That makes sense.

163
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:42,220
Oh, make sure to take some pictures!

164
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:43,060
Huh?

165
00:10:43,061 --> 00:10:45,930
Not of you, but of Saeki-kun!

166
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:48,520
Well, have fun on your pilgrimage!

167
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,020
Let's go home.

168
00:10:59,903 --> 00:11:02,373
The greenery is getting so lush.

169
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,879
Oh, look, there are
mountains over there too.

170
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:05,880
Yeah.

171
00:11:07,217 --> 00:11:09,076
Coming out here
really feels like a mini getaway.

172
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:11,120
Right?
I'm starting to get really excited.

173
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:13,260
This is great.

174
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:17,340
But the itinerary you
made is absolutely perfect.

175
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:21,219
And the movie "Sea of Light"
feels very much like your style.

176
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,719
- Really?
- Yeah.

177
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:26,310
It's Director Zaizen's masterpiece.
I figured you'd like it too.

178
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:29,380
Yeah, but it has a real indie vibe.

179
00:11:29,770 --> 00:11:33,900
Though I doubt many people
go on pilgrimages for that movie anymore.

180
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:37,610
But to me,
it's a very important film.

181
00:11:38,150 --> 00:11:39,170
Oh?

182
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:43,570
It really resonated with me.

183
00:11:44,060 --> 00:11:45,740
I felt like a part of me was saved by it.

184
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,200
I see.

185
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,000
Wow, this is the place.

186
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,120
It looks exactly like it did in the movie.

187
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,720
Of course it does.
This is where they filmed it.

188
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:06,740
Even though it's an unstaffed station now,

189
00:12:07,020 --> 00:12:09,620
I heard they still use it for
commercials sometimes.

190
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:16,666
I thought there'd be other tourists,
but we have the whole place to ourselves.

191
00:12:16,690 --> 00:12:19,110
Yeah, it's like our own private station.

192
00:12:19,690 --> 00:12:22,120
Oh, let me take a picture.

193
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,510
Oh, me too.

194
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,450
- Oh, nice.
- Looks great.

195
00:12:29,940 --> 00:12:32,460
Wow, that looks beautiful.

196
00:12:35,940 --> 00:12:36,630
Wataru.

197
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:37,630
Hmm?

198
00:12:38,310 --> 00:12:39,310
Ah, hey!

199
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:41,590
Got a great shot.

200
00:12:41,590 --> 00:12:42,590
Honestly...

201
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,200
Hey.

202
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,820
Want to try acting out that scene?

203
00:12:51,180 --> 00:12:55,500
The scene where the protagonist gets out of prison
and someone talks to him for the first time.

204
00:12:55,690 --> 00:12:56,810
Sure.

205
00:12:58,940 --> 00:13:01,270
Where did you come from?

206
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:04,969
Wait a second.

207
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:06,019
That was spot on!

208
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:08,199
Don't just laugh.
Answer me.

209
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,780
I can't. Hold on.

210
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:11,030
My stomach hurts from laughing.

211
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,389
What's so funny anyway?

212
00:13:14,390 --> 00:13:17,060
Hold on. It's just that you
sounded way too much like him.

213
00:13:18,620 --> 00:13:19,620
That was hilarious.

214
00:13:21,980 --> 00:13:26,740
His journey to find the parents who
abandoned him started right here, didn't it?

215
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:33,536
Let's go check out the
outside of the station too.

216
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:34,560
Okay.

217
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:44,839
The air is so fresh.

218
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:46,060
It really is.

219
00:13:48,660 --> 00:13:51,510
This view really purifies the soul.

220
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,589
Is your soul really that dirty?

221
00:13:53,590 --> 00:13:54,700
No, that's not it.

222
00:13:55,060 --> 00:13:57,979
I'm just putting myself
in the protagonist's shoes.

223
00:13:57,980 --> 00:13:59,200
I know.

224
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,606
Since we're here,
should we take some videos?

225
00:14:01,630 --> 00:14:02,860
Oh, sure.

226
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:04,919
Then should I try
walking with some dramatic flair?

227
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:05,920
Yeah.

228
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,470
And... action!

229
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,140
What are you laughing at?

230
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,779
What's with that serious face?

231
00:14:17,780 --> 00:14:19,916
I told you, I was trying to
walk with some dramatic flair.

232
00:14:19,940 --> 00:14:21,040
Wait, try walking again.

233
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:23,380
And... action!

234
00:14:26,020 --> 00:14:27,160
Nice expression.

235
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:28,720
Oh.

236
00:14:32,530 --> 00:14:33,240
Did it turn out well?

237
00:14:33,241 --> 00:14:34,841
Did you try to be funny at the very end?

238
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:39,939
Here you go.
Sorry to keep you waiting.

239
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:40,940
Thank you.

240
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:43,500
Oh, thank you.

241
00:14:44,130 --> 00:14:45,700
Let's eat!

242
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:48,420
Mmm, let's try the broth first.

243
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,400
Delicious.

244
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:57,340
What is this?

245
00:14:59,270 --> 00:15:00,270
Mmm!

246
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,240
This is amazing!

247
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:05,250
These noodles are so chewy.

248
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:08,360
Saeki, don't just film.
Eat up.

249
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,100
It's really good.

250
00:15:10,950 --> 00:15:11,950
Yeah.

251
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:19,470
So good.
This broth is incredible.

252
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:25,590
Mmm, delicious.

253
00:15:26,340 --> 00:15:27,590
- It's good, right?
- Yeah.

254
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:29,550
This is seriously amazing.

255
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,640
- It was totally worth the trip.
- Definitely.

256
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,520
The seaweed is delicious too.

257
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,040
The bamboo shoots are great too.

258
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,520
Incredible.
These must all be local specialties.

259
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:41,519
I feel alive again.

260
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:42,730
Really.

261
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:45,110
Yours looks delicious too.

262
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,480
It is.

263
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:49,780
Let me have a bite.

264
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:52,900
Yum.

265
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:54,800
Do you want a bite of mine too?

266
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,799
- How is it?
- Delicious.

267
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,560
Good, right?

268
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:08,000
You've got to have
an icy treat in the summer.

269
00:16:08,170 --> 00:16:09,170
Yeah.

270
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:13,640
Ow, brain freeze!

271
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:15,390
Are you okay?

272
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:19,220
No, this is a bit... I'm fine.

273
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,080
This is nice.

274
00:16:22,620 --> 00:16:23,639
So relaxing.

275
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:24,640
Yeah.

276
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,079
Ah, this feels great.

277
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,080
Yeah.

278
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:32,300
Wow, what a view.

279
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:35,899
Wow, it's beautiful.

280
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:36,900
It really is.

281
00:16:38,726 --> 00:16:41,696
Wow, the water is so clear.

282
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,120
Wow, amazing.

283
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,399
It's absolutely gorgeous.

284
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,400
Right?

285
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,030
Hey, want to go down there?

286
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:54,130
Huh?

287
00:16:54,131 --> 00:16:56,050
Why not? Let's go play in the water.

288
00:16:58,380 --> 00:17:00,860
- This feels great.
- How dare you splash me!

289
00:17:00,890 --> 00:17:03,700
- Stop it!
- You're splashing pretty hard.

290
00:17:04,350 --> 00:17:05,350
Stop!

291
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:08,020
Hey, you're dead meat!

292
00:17:09,540 --> 00:17:11,579
Hey, I'm really going to fall!

293
00:17:11,580 --> 00:17:12,800
You'll be fine.

294
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:16,299
Hey, okay!
I get it.

295
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:17,899
Okay, okay, let's take a break.

296
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:18,900
Alright, alright.

297
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:20,660
- Let's take a break.
- Let's take a break.

298
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,680
The water is freezing.

299
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:26,800
Hey.

300
00:17:27,660 --> 00:17:29,620
- Seriously...
- Let's skip stones.

301
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:30,380
Huh?

302
00:17:30,381 --> 00:17:31,709
- Skipping stones.
- Skipping stones?

303
00:17:31,710 --> 00:17:33,219
Have you never skipped stones before?

304
00:17:33,220 --> 00:17:34,220
No.

305
00:17:35,050 --> 00:17:36,896
This might actually be my first time
playing by a river.

306
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:37,930
Seriously?

307
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:40,349
Didn't you do this when you were a kid?

308
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:42,200
No, almost never.

309
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:44,639
I always stayed indoors during holidays.

310
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:49,020
I see. I was the exact opposite.
I was always playing outside.

311
00:17:50,540 --> 00:17:51,980
Isn't there Higashimura Park?

312
00:17:52,530 --> 00:17:53,880
I used to go there all the time.

313
00:17:58,450 --> 00:17:59,450
Saeki?

314
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:00,530
What's wrong?

315
00:18:00,531 --> 00:18:01,700
Nothing.

316
00:18:03,060 --> 00:18:04,890
I'm just really happy right now.

317
00:18:06,220 --> 00:18:08,330
I'm glad.

318
00:18:10,780 --> 00:18:14,969
But honestly, I'm the one who's
getting a bit too carried away.

319
00:18:14,970 --> 00:18:16,470
- Woah!
- Watch out!

320
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:18,490
Sorry. Thanks for saving me.

321
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:30,220
Wataru, don't be so tense.

322
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:31,830
It's making me nervous too.

323
00:18:38,210 --> 00:18:39,410
Don't ask for the impossible.

324
00:18:40,710 --> 00:18:41,930
I can stand on my own now.

325
00:18:41,970 --> 00:18:43,040
Thanks.

326
00:18:48,950 --> 00:18:50,050
Saeki?

327
00:18:51,670 --> 00:18:52,770
Um...

328
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:56,020
Can we stay like this
for just a little longer?

329
00:19:08,850 --> 00:19:11,050
I didn't see anything
about there being rain.

330
00:19:11,090 --> 00:19:13,020
- Hurry up, Saeki.
- Okay.

331
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:18,810
Damn, we got pretty soaked.

332
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:22,626
It probably wouldn't have been much different
if we had actually fallen into the river.

333
00:19:22,650 --> 00:19:24,230
Don't say that.

334
00:19:24,290 --> 00:19:26,700
And after you just saved me, too.

335
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:38,070
It's just a sudden afternoon shower.

336
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:51,870
I'm really looking forward to
the ocean view in the final scene.

337
00:19:51,970 --> 00:19:53,770
Finally reaching the truth.

338
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:55,610
That's an iconic scene.

339
00:19:56,150 --> 00:19:57,780
Yeah, it is.

340
00:19:57,990 --> 00:19:59,190
I'm looking forward to it too.

341
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,860
It really feels like summer.

342
00:20:09,410 --> 00:20:11,170
I really love summer.

343
00:20:13,570 --> 00:20:16,800
Summer is special to me too.

344
00:20:17,690 --> 00:20:18,730
Special?

345
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,630
Because it's the season I met you, Wataru.

346
00:20:26,170 --> 00:20:27,170
You...

347
00:20:27,450 --> 00:20:29,620
Don't say embarrassing things like that.

348
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:34,080
By the way, was it summer
when we met at the record store?

349
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:36,750
Yeah, it was summer then too.

350
00:20:37,770 --> 00:20:39,070
I just wanted to say it.

351
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:41,046
You don't have to
take it seriously, Wataru.

352
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:42,490
How could I not take it seriously?

353
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:47,550
You might be used to
this kind of thing, Saeki,

354
00:20:47,970 --> 00:20:50,510
but with zero dating experience,
I have no immunity.

355
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,840
Don't make me say it out loud.
It's depressing.

356
00:20:54,590 --> 00:20:58,670
But Wataru, you're the first
person I've ever confessed to.

357
00:20:59,210 --> 00:21:00,210
Seriously?

358
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:01,350
Yeah.

359
00:21:01,351 --> 00:21:02,749
Because before, I was always
the one being confessed to.

360
00:21:02,750 --> 00:21:05,180
Oh, bragging now, are we?

361
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,450
But you're amazing.

362
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:13,740
I wouldn't have the courage
to confess so casually.

363
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:29,260
For me, it wasn't so much courage
as it was determination.

364
00:21:40,190 --> 00:21:41,190
I see.

365
00:21:52,910 --> 00:21:57,370
I know it must be confusing
to suddenly have a friend confess to you.

366
00:21:58,810 --> 00:22:01,210
If it makes things awkward for you,
there's nothing I can do.

367
00:22:04,370 --> 00:22:06,050
I don't think that way at all.

368
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:08,340
Huh?

369
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:11,590
I don't think it's awkward.

370
00:22:12,310 --> 00:22:15,830
Though it was definitely
one of the biggest shocks of my life.

371
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:21,270
But regardless of whether
you're a guy or a girl,

372
00:22:22,570 --> 00:22:24,770
to be liked by someone like you, Saeki...

373
00:22:25,990 --> 00:22:28,240
It makes me feel like
I'm not so bad after all.

374
00:22:34,170 --> 00:22:35,270
Don't worry.

375
00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:38,310
If I didn't like it,
I would've just said so.

376
00:22:47,530 --> 00:22:50,470
It's been a while since I heard that.

377
00:22:51,850 --> 00:22:53,750
Huh? Really?

378
00:22:56,230 --> 00:22:57,230
Yeah.

379
00:23:07,230 --> 00:23:10,500
The reason I don't mind it
must be because it's him.

380
00:23:15,110 --> 00:23:16,110
Wataru.

381
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:19,250
Yeah?

382
00:23:22,210 --> 00:23:23,360
I like you.

383
00:23:32,150 --> 00:23:33,380
I know already.

384
00:23:39,450 --> 00:23:43,980
At the time, I still pretended
not to notice that feeling.

385
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:45,900
(Next Episode)

386
00:24:45,970 --> 00:24:50,269
Anyone would be annoyed seeing the person they
like getting all cozy with someone else, right?

387
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:52,630
I just thought you looked
cute when you were sulking.

388
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:55,920
I want you to follow your heart.

389
00:24:55,990 --> 00:24:59,660
With someone expressing their
feelings so passionately, even I...

